Edward discovered drum'n'bass during the late '90s but didn't release his first production until 2012.
He made his proper debut that November, when he appeared on Hospital Records' Sick Music 3 compilation with "Give It Up," an emotive track laced with multiple melodic keyboard lines.

The similarly emotive "Spoken" was placed on Hospitality Drum & Bass 2013 in January 2013His eponymous debut album Etherwood was released on 4 November 2013 through Hospital Records' imprint label Med School.
He was described by Nozstock: The Hidden Valley as "undoubtedly one of the most promising young talents in the scene today".
